- Static method

+ a Static methods can't access instance methods and instance variables

+ Usually used for operations that don't require any data from an instance
of the class (from 'this'). Which means we cannot use "this" in static methods

+ When a method doesn't use instance variables, that method should be declared as
static method


- Instance method

+ Belongs to an instance of a class

+ an instance method we have to initialise the class first usually by
using the new keyword

+ Can access instance methods and instance variables directly.

+ Can access static methods and static variables directly